  },
  "description": {
    "en": "Build a tool that merges multiple PDF files into one — perfect for reports, invoices, or study notes.",
    "ta": "பல PDF கோப்புகளை ஒன்றாக இணைக்கும் கருவியை உருவாக்குங்கள் — அறிக்கைகள், விலைப்பட்டியல்கள் அல்லது படிப்பு குறிப்புகளுக்கு சரியானது."
  },
  "xp_reward": 55,
  "story_variants": {
    "en": "## Merge PDFs Like a Boss\n\nYou've got 10 PDF invoices that need to become one file. Or 5 chapters of notes to combine before an exam. Doing it manually? That's what non-programmers do.\n\n### What You'll Learn\n- Installing packages with `pip`\n- Working with `PyPDF2` library\n- File I/O with context managers (`with` statement)\n- Command-line arguments with `sys.argv`\n\n### The Plan\n1. Accept a list of PDF filenames\n2. Open each PDF and read its pages\n3. Add all pages to a new PDF writer\n4. Save the merged result\n\n> **Practical value:** This is a tool you'll genuinely use. Many paid apps charge $5/month for this — you'll build it in 15 lines!"
  },
